<br>
When you go to a store to purchase lets say a case of soda. A case of soda contains 24 cans. If you then get home and your case of soda contains 22 cans of soda instead. Now there are a few things you could do. <br>
<br>
1) You could go to the store and tell them &quot;Hey I paid for 24 cans of soda and only got 22 cans..where is my other 2 cans&quot;<br>
<br>
2) You could say &quot;Well it is only 2 cans of soda no biggie&quot;<br>
<br>
3) Ask for a refund so that you can buy a new case of soda with all 24 cans inside.<br>
<br>
From a customer service stand point they should refund the points. The description said 60secs, and magicians purchased the skill with the intentions that it would last 60secs. It only seems fair to me. Since they are not willing to give mages the other 32secs that they advertised then at the very least they should refund the money (points)to the mages that were cheated.<br>
<br>
If I go to a store and the ad says one thing and when I get home with what I have purchased, and didn't receive all that was promissed in the ad then I want a refund or the rest of what was promissed. So calling people spoiled for wanting SoE to behave like most other companies do in terms of customer service is rude. They are wrong and they should refund the points.<br>
